## **২. Monitoring Agent Auto-Install**

### **Option A: Zabbix Agent**

1. Download Zabbix Agent MSI (latest stable)

```powershell
Invoke-WebRequest -Uri "https://cdn.zabbix.com/zabbix/binaries/stable/6.4/6.4.11/zabbix_agent-6.4.11-windows-amd64-openssl.msi" -OutFile "C:\Temp\zabbix_agent.msi"
```

2. Install silently:

```powershell
Start-Process msiexec.exe -ArgumentList "/i C:\Temp\zabbix_agent.msi /quiet /norestart /l*v install.log" -Wait
```

3. Configure Agent to point to Zabbix Server:

```powershell
Set-Content -Path "C:\Program Files\Zabbix Agent\zabbix_agentd.conf" -Value "Server=192.168.10.100`nServerActive=192.168.10.100`nHostname=$(hostname)"
Restart-Service "Zabbix Agent"
```

### **Option B: Nagios NRPE**

1. Download and install NRPE Windows service
2. Configure with Nagios server IP
3. Start service automatically

💡 **Tip:** Zabbix is easier for Windows-centric networks.

